cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with optimization problems in machine learning, specifically with non-convex and non-differentiable constraints. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also discusses fairness metrics, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and other goals such as accuracy, coverage, recall, and churn, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
